column31: Measles has been the subject of much debate, and a lot of it is due to the myths surrounding it. Hopefully, this helps clear some up. Measles has an incubation period of 7 - 21 days, averaging 10 - 12. It is NOT, contrary to popular belief, contagious until symptoms appear. (It *is* contagious prior to when the rash begins, there are 1 - 3 days of fever, cough, runny nose, and general flu-like symptoms before the rash appears.) A lot of kids will experience "complications" like diarrhea or ear infection, but these are generally mild. Serious complications are fairly rare, and more common in children with compromised immune systems. There's some evidence, on a population level, that measles infection seems to increase the risk of subsequent infections in the next several months, but no one really knows why. One large study in Britain showed that children who got measles were already more likely to visit the doctor/have sick days prior to measles infection, and were even more likely after. Some sort of underlying immune dysfunction may play a role in this. But, all studies have focused on population-level data and no one has examined individual cases or figured out what is really going on here. The measles vaccine was licensed in 1963. It is a live-virus vaccine. (The inactivated virus version wasn't effective in preventing measles, and many children ended up with atypical measles later, so it was never approved.) It was the measles portion of the vaccine that was potentially implicated in the now-infamous 1998 Wakefield study. That study was tiny, covering only 12 children, and looked at colitis diagnoses in children with autism. 8 of the mothers reported that their children's symptoms began after an MMR vaccine, and it was noted that the vaccine strain of measles was found in their bowels. Wakefield noted this in his research and recommended that follow-up studies be done to explore this correlation. He DID NOT conclude that vaccines caused autism and that was not the point of the study! Today, we still don't have solid data on the risks of the vaccine. We know there is DNA contamination in it, and this could cause DNA changes/damages. We know there are thousands and thousands of similar reports of chronic diarrhea, loss of speech and coordination, following the MMR. Proper studies aren't being done. We also know that any protection, once assumed to be life-long, wanes after 15 - 20 years, leaving adults (who are more likely to have complications) susceptible to infection. We also know that babies born to vaccinated mothers have a significantly lower duration of protection from maternal antibodies than babies born to naturally-immune mothers. This can shift disease burden to young infants, where it is also more serious. Sources: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/26103708:=:https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26103708/ https://www.cdc.gov/vaccines/pubs/pinkbook/meas.html https://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/volumes/67/wr/mm6740a3.htm https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2677258/ https://academic.oup.com/jid/article/206/10/1542/858893 https://www.bmj.com/content/362/bmj.k3976/rr-11 https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/26597262:=:https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26597262/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6231568/

column31: There has been a lot of controversy surrounding hydroxychloroquine for months, and as a natural health company who is also strongly in favor of medical freedom, we wanted to make it clear where we stand. Hydroxychloroquine is NOT necessarily a miracle drug and we're not recommending anyone take it. There are MANY herbal remedies out there that can help, as well as zinc, selenium, and vitamins C and D. Supporting the body naturally is absolutely the best way to go. BUT we stand firmly against the censorship of science. We're not okay with some group of people deciding what information we can or can't have access to. We're not okay with people who can't or won't use natural remedies dying when they don't have to, just because data has been suppressed. We still don't love Big Pharma. column31: In Part Two of his four-part series, Dr. Palmer notes we are currently seeing the practical nature of the historical "is it the germ or the terrain" debate playing out with the COVID-19 pandemic. "I am not saying that the virus (germ) is not real and to be considered, but more important than the pathogen is the resistance of the host. Some people get COVID-19 and do not develop symptoms (some estimates as high as 50% or more) or have mild symptoms. On the other hand, some people are overcome by the virus." It is no wonder that large cities with populations that have higher rates of those predisposing illnesses and high population density are hit harder. History is repeating itself albeit to a lesser degree. Our modern cities are nowhere as bad environmentally as early in the last century, but they do have certain similar characteristics.

column31: You may have heard that zinc benefits include helping people recovering from colds, but this mineral is also needed by those who aren’t sick and who don’t have compromised immune function. Ideally this essential mineral should be consumed in small amounts every day in order to maintain overall health and perform hundreds of important functions. What are the benefits of taking zinc, as well as consuming foods high in zinc? Zinc benefits the body in many ways — it helps with hormone production, proper growth and repair, improved immunity and promoting normal digestion. It also has the ability to act as an anti-inflammatory agent, which means that it may have significant therapeutic benefits for several common, chronic diseases like cancer or heart disease, among other zinc benefits. No wonder zinc deficiency can lead to a number of health issues, such as chronic fatigue, digestive issues and hormonal problems. How does zinc help your body exactly? It’s actually present within all bodily tissues and needed for healthy cell division. It acts like an antioxidant within the body, fighting free-radical damage and helping slow the aging process. This mineral also has a major impact on hormonal balance, so for this reason, even a small deficiency can result in an increased risk for infertility or diabetes. According to researchers at the Department of Dermatology at the University of California: Zinc plays an essential role in numerous biochemical pathways: organ systems, including the integumentary, gastrointestinal, central nervous system, immune, skeletal, and reproductive systems… Zinc deficiency results in dysfunction of both humoral and cell-mediated immunity and increases the susceptibility to infection. If you have low intake of zinc, it’s possible to experience negative reactions like frequently getting sick, feeling like you’re always tired and run down, and dealing with poor concentration, stunted growth and the inability to heal wounds.

column31: Disclaimer: Fragrances are not everywhere, they are in places we choose and have control of such as our homes and vehicles. Let's empower taking control of our health, environment and bodies 👏 Fragrances are linked to a staggering number of health risks. Across multiple research studies, chemicals used to make fragrances are classified as allergens, hormone disruptors, asthma triggers, neurotoxins & carcinogens. The punchline: fragrances are highly toxic. Fragrances commonly contain phthalates, which are chemicals that help the scents last longer. Health risks for phthalates are startling and include cancer, human reproductive and developmental toxicity, endocrine disruption, birth defects & respiratory problems. These toxic villains are very hard to avoid because manufacturers are not required to list them on ingredient labels. Fragrance chemicals, like other toxic chemicals, can pass from the skin and into the blood. Manufacturers are not required to list their fragrance ingredients on product labels. Often only one word, “fragrance”, is used on the label and can hide a cocktail of more than 100 toxic ingredients. This is because fragrances are considered to be “trade secrets”. The fragrance industry regulates itself, so that safety testing does not have to be confirmed by regulators before products are sold to consumers. So called “natural fragrances” can be just as toxic as synthetic fragrances. Whether it’s in a cleaning product, hand sanitizer, soap, make-up, deodorant, shampoo, or laundry detergent, fragrance chemicals aren’t actually making your product perform better – they are just giving you that perception. We’ve been trained to think that clean has a smell, when in truth that’s not the case. Fragrances are linked to so many profound health risks that avoiding them is probably the #1 change you can make to reduce your family’s exposure to toxic chemicals. To avoid fragrances, the Environmental Working Group advises that consumers read the word “fragrance” or “parfum” and translate it to mean “hidden chemicals”. The safest choice is to always choose fragrance-free products such as Young Living. But a couple of key tips you should keep in mind: Don’t be fooled by products labeled with “natural fragrance,” because there is no standard criteria for what these words mean. These can be just as un-safe as fragrances not described this way, so skip these products too. If you see the words “fragrance-free” or “unscented”, your Spidey senses should kick into action. You also have to check the ingredient list, because sometimes manufacturers use masking fragrances to cover the chemical smell of their products. I recently discovered an independent, peer-reviewed study that was published in the American Thoracic Society’s American Journal of Respiratory and Critical Care Medicine {link below}. Here are the cliff notes: ✨ The study {based on 20 years of research} shows that cleaning your home with national brand cleaners significantly damages your lung tissue. ✨ Almost all of the cleaning products that are available at the grocery store include many harmful chemicals including ammonia, chlorine bleach and other disinfectant compounds. ✨ This study included over 6000 male and female subjects with the average age of 34 at the beginning of the study and 54 at the conclusion of it. ✨ Subjects used both spray and liquid home cleaning products. ✨ Lung capacity was tested regularly. ✨ Results were compiled by 28 top researchers from 9 different countries. ✨ This study found that women are affected far more than men….which makes perfect sense since women typically use more cleaning products than men. ✨ Cleaning at home is just as harmful as being an occupational cleaner if not more so. The “cleaning at home” group saw the same decrease in lung health as the“occupational cleaning” group. ✨ Another finding - Liquid cleaners are just as dangerous as sprays. The researchers originally suspected that products in a spray would be more harmful/dangerous than those applied as a liquid, gel or wipe. Not true according to the study...all are harmful. There is a better way. 🌿✨ How FULL of gratitude I am for a wonderful cleaner that is safe, effective, budget friendly and is IMMUNE boosting. Children can use it and you can use it around pets. it smells delightful. And it's not poisoning us every time we use it. I would love happy and healthy lungs for my family and me for the rest of our lives. 🌱+SOLUTION! Thieves Household Cleaner is made from organic seed to seal herbs and plants, never animal tested and works much better than Lysol, Clorox, Windex, Mr. Clean, Method, Mrs. Meyers, etc... Friends, it comes to LESS than $1 per bottle! It’s INCREDIBLE. column31: Robert F. Kennedy, Jr.: When i was a boy, it was unthinkable that an American liberal would acquiesce to censorship. It was axiomatic that all the Nazi atrocities had begun with censorship and silencing of critics of government policies. Our civics teachers taught that the free flow of information —even inconvenient truths— was the lifeblood of democracy. My uncle JFK commented in 1962 that American “libraries should be open to all—except the censor. We must know all the facts and hear all the alternatives and listen to all the criticisms. Let us welcome controversial books and controversial authors. For the Bill of Rights is the guardian of our security as well as our liberty.” History will record that,in 2020, it was men who called themselves “liberal” who lead the clamor for censorship. Harry Truman warned us against such men: “Once a government is committed to the principle of silencing the voice of opposition, it has only one way to go, and that is down the path of increasingly repressive measures, until it becomes a source of terror to all its citizens and creates a country where everyone lives in fear." In March 2019 Democratic Congressman Adam Schiff asked each of these powerful Internet titans to censor “vaccine misinformation”, a euphemism for any statement that departs from official declarations by Pharma and it’s captured regulatory officials. Each of these Silicon Valley tyrants is partnered in rich deals with vaccine makers. They were therefore delighted to comply. Today they openly silence the tragic stories of American mothers of vaccine injured children and all other unapproved criticism of pharmaceutical products.Where does Adam Schiff thinks this will end? Does he imagine Bill Gates as a friend of liberty? In one short moment,the worm will turn. To Schiff, I paraphrase St Thomas Moore’s query; “When you have obliterated the First Amendment to get at the Devil, and the Devil then turns on you, then where will you hide?”

column31: "Government officials keep rolling their eyes and assigning rude slurs to people who won't just do what they say. Hey! If you want our cooperation, then you'd better change how you're treating us. Here's what we're looking for.... Show Us the Data Making proclamations based on assumptions, incomplete science, or numbers that aren't adding up isn't good enough. Show us the studies, how you're collecting the data, what exactly you used to come to your conclusions. Put all the info online so we can review it ourselves. Acknowledge Subtleties Things aren't black and white. Maybe some things are beneficial in some situations, or when done certain ways, but not others. Don't make blanket statements anymore. Tell us the WHOLE truth. We don't need the message broken down into soundbites. Apologize if You're Wrong Sometimes, you're going to make a bad decision based on faulty data, or let the stress get to you. You're human, we get that. But when it happens, take responsibility and apologize for it. Don't just pretend that your flip-flopping or harsh statements were justified or that they didn't happen. Hear Our Concerns You CANNOT make simple rules that apply across the board. People have different situations, needs, and concerns. Listen to them. Make space for them. Don't dismiss people with concerns as childish, ignorant, or difficult. Take them seriously. Be Respectful We're sure it's hard to be a leader right now, with everyone as divided as they are. But your job is to bring people together, not pit them against one another. Do not encourage people to report each other. Do not call your constituents names. Speak respectfully of everyone. Be the example. Ask Us, Don't Order Us We're not children. We're capable of understanding the situation, looking at all the facts, and coming to our own conclusions. We don't want to be ordered around. If there's something you think would be beneficial, then lay out the facts, and ask us respectfully. The people who can, probably will. Our issue with everything has never been that we think it's all just some conspiracy theory, or that we don't want to take care of other people, or that we're being contrary just to be contrary. We're not convinced by the science, we don't feel respected, and we're worried about what the future holds. Come to the table with us as equals, and we'll be more likely to hear what you have to say. Keep insulting us and acting like we're idiots, well...prepare to be opposed forever.

How Magnesium Boosts Your Immune System
Magnesium clearly has a profound impact on your overall health. But one aspect of its impact on the body that has spiked interest in researchers is the immune system. Magnesium, specifically magnesium chloride is shown to not just support the body’s immune system, but strengthen it. It can help stimulate and increase efficiency in combating illness and disease.

Without magnesium, studies have found your body’s natural immune responses can be negatively impacted. On the flip side, they have also shown that having sufficient amounts of magnesium in your system can boost natural immune responses and have some involvement in reducing inflammation, apoptosis, etc. Magnesium has also shown to play a role in oxidative stress, which can have a large negative impact on your immune system if not properly managed.

There’s still research that needs to be done in order to really place a finger on what it is that gives magnesium its fascinating effect on your immune system. But it has become clear that it does have a worthwhile impact and we can be sure that your immune system - and your overall health - does much better with #magnesium than without.

column31: We recently learned about an organization called “Stop Hate for Profit.” Their goal sounds admirable – they want to stop racism, anti-Semitism, and other forms of hate in the world. Unfortunately, they chose to extend their mission to “combating vaccine misinformation” and other topics that are a matter of scientific debate, not hate at all. And, their method of accomplishing this is to ask Facebook to simply ban all groups that discuss any ideas they don’t like. Censorship is NOT the way forward. We do not believe that shutting down discussion or debate on vaccines is rational or logical. This, and other contentious topics, are matters that are not, no matter what the mainstream claims, open and shut. There are many considerations, and healthy debate and examination of conflicting evidence MUST be had. As far as racism and anti-Semitism, we stand against these and all other forms of hate. Banning people and groups will do nothing to change hate. It will only force people onto other platforms, to breed echo chambers that lead to more hate. Pretending that people who think in certain ways don’t exist doesn’t change how they feel, and some studies show that feeling they are being treated unfairly will only lead to them digging in their heels more. We believe that all ideas should be spoken, discussed, shared, and challenged where needed. Only by opening up the lines of communication, and asking people to listen to lived experiences and painful stories can we change hearts and minds. Censorship cannot accomplish that. Because of “Stop the Hate’s” message of abject censorship, we do not support them. We want to see a world where people can feel strong enough to use their voices and look for connection and help people learn new and better ways voluntarily, and discuss science honestly. We want open discussion instead of battle lines and othering. column31: It was 1976. Mark Waldvogel, a healthy, athletic high school senior in Kailua, Hawaii, heeded the Government's warnings about a possible deadly epidemic and so he got a swine flu vaccination. He felt it was his patriotic duty. Two weeks after receiving the vaccination, Mr. Waldvogel became paralyzed from the chest down. He was a victim of Guillain‐Barre Syndrome (sometimes called French polio), a rare neurological disorder that doctors concluded had been caused by the vaccine. Two years later, in an interview with The NY Times, Mr. Waldvogel, 20 years old, is a paraplegic, confined to a wheelchair for life. Mr. Waldvogel was not alone. He was one of approximately 500 claims for Guillain barre syndrome alone. There were 4,000 people who sought damages from the government for medical problems triggered by that one flu shot. It all started in February 1976, when four recruits at Fort Dix, NJ fell ill with an influenza-like illness. At first it was thought to be adenovirus, which caused an outbreak the previous month. But when one of the men, 19-year-old Private David Lewis collapsed and died--after he was forced to leave his sick bed to make a five-mile night march, the New Jersey lab sent isolates to the CDC’s Bureau of Laboratories. There, isolates were confirmed to be swine-type influenza A viruses. They feared this was the same virus that caused the 1918 flu pandemic that killed 50 million people worldwide. (It wouldn’t be until the 2000’s that gene sequencing of that 1918 virus was of avian origin, and more recently possibly equine or an unidentified mammalian host.) While the World Health Organization wanted to take a wait and see approach, the US government urgently set out to make a new vaccine for this potentially deadly virus. By mid-March, 200 million doses of vaccines were ordered by federal health officials. But one hang-up, vaccine makers would not make this vaccine unless the government gave them complete protection from all liability, including injuries associated with the shot. They wanted complete indemnity, and they got it. They also got it in 1986 against every vaccine given to children today. Bracing for the storm, public health officials predicted deadly outbreaks in the coming winter. Health “experts" estimated that the deadly virus could infect 50 to 60 million Americans. Hospitals suspended non-essential medical procedures. President Gerald Ford embarked on a zealous campaign to vaccinate “every man, woman, and child in the United States.” The first vaccines became available in October. Photos of celebrities and political figures receiving the flu shot appeared in the media. But the storm clouds had begun to form. Within a few weeks of the national vaccine campaign, in early October, on the same day, three elderly people died suddenly after they received the vaccine at the same Pittsburgh clinic. Two of the families consented to autopsies and it was found that they died of heart attacks. CDC epidemiologists investigated and “found no evidence to suggest the deaths were caused by the vaccine.” But the body count began to rise. The next day, a newspaper reported that 14 people in 9 states had died within 48 hours of receiving the flu shot, and again, there was no evidence linking any of the deaths to the vaccine. Within a few days, that number was up to 33 and by October 22, 41 died shortly after vaccination. In December, cases of Guillain-Barre syndrome began making the news. Ninety-four cases of paralysis had been reported in 14 states, the majority of cases in recently vaccinated people. Of those, four people died. With nearly 25% of the US population, or 45 million citizens, vaccinated against swine flu, the vaccine program was reluctantly suspended. Final body count: over 40 people died, approximately 500 people developed Guillain-Barre syndrome, and several thousand were injured by the vaccine. The pandemic never materialized as predicted: only 200 cases of swine flu and one death was reported in the United States. Like salt in a wound, the incidence of swine flu among the vaccinated was seven times greater than it was among those who had not been vaccinated. #swineflu #pandemic #vaccine #outbreak #guillainbarre #covid_19 #COVID19 #plandemic #vaccinesafety #OperationWarpSpeed

column31: This is interesting! Hospitals in several countries saw dips in premature births, which could be a starting point for future research. It started with doctors in Ireland and Denmark. Each team, unaware of the other’s work, crunched the numbers from its own region or country and found that during the lockdowns, premature births — especially the earliest, most dangerous cases — had plummeted. The researchers found that during the lockdown, the rate of babies born before 28 weeks had dropped by a startling 90 percent. They speculate that by staying home, some pregnant women may have experienced less stress from work and commuting, gotten more sleep and received more support from their families, the researchers said. Women staying at home also could have avoided infections in general. Further research might help doctors, scientists and parents-to-be understand the causes of premature birth and ways to prevent it. https://www.nytimes.com/2020/07/19/health/coronavirus-premature-birth.html

column31: The Wilderness Act stipulates, "There shall be no commercial enterprise . . . within any wilderness area designated by this Act." Does a cellular company need to have a physical presence within designated wilderness to be conducting a commercial enterprise there? The law isn't clear. A possible analogue is aviation; pilots are required to maintain an altitude of at least 2,000 feet when flying over wilderness. This is an example of an activity that doesn't have a permanent physical presence in wilderness yet still has restrictions placed on it because the activity can have an impact on the wilderness experience.

column31: The syringe has an interesting history. I dug into it. Didn’t mean to write a 4,500 word article but you pull a string and the whole garment unravels. I want to put these longer articles into podcasts so people can listen to them. The word syringe comes from the Greek word syrinx, meaning “tube”, and dates back to the 1st century AD. The early instruments required the skin to be cut first, and their primary function was to drain fluid, pus or foreign bodies from cavities and abscesses. The idea of the hollow needle and syringe (which wouldn't come until 1844) was inspired by the stinger of a bee. I knew it was. And then I found the reference. It’s based off of poisonous insects and animals, whose venom attacks the central nervous system. We can’t escape it. It’s always going to have the potential to cause harm. It’s an injection. Observing insects and animals with fangs or stingers is probably what compelled early humans to make a ‘poison needle’ as a weapon in the form of the blowpipe and poison dipped arrows what was used by practically every indigenous and ancient culture for thousands of years. Arrows or darts were dipped in poisons (which are nerve agents) from plants or animals, and blown through a pipe to pierce the skin of enemies. The poison quickly spreads to the central nervous system, causing the aforementioned paralysis, death etc. In 1844 Irish physician and surgeon Francis Rynd created the first hollow needle for subcutaneous injection of morphine to treat a female patient who had suffered for years with severe pain in her face due to neuralgia, which is damaged nerves. When drinking morphine to kill the pain didn’t work, Rynd tried the more direct route of injecting the morphine under her skin closer to the damaged facial nerves. Pain relief was achieved and this new technique was quickly and widely accepted. It was credited as: “The greatest boon to medicine since the discovery of chloroform.” A few years later in 1853, Scottish physician Alexander Wood and French surgeon Charles Gabriel Pravaz added to the design to make the first true hypodermic syringe. He was inspired by the stinger of the bee. Read more: https://circleofmamas.com/health-news/injecting-poisons-a-history-of-the-syringe/

column31: You have the right to do whatever it takes to protect yourself. You can wear a mask. You can get a vaccine. You can stay away from other people/large gatherings. You can stay home. You can take supplements. You can tell others not to come to your home or to wear a mask in your home. You can wash your hands. You can eat healthy food. You can get a blood test done to see if you have any nutrient deficiencies and correct them. You can do whatever you want to protect yourself and your family. You CANNOT require other people to take action to protect your family. And if you demand they do and they try to tell you that they have a situation where they can't do that and you say "Well then that makes you selfish!" you are the problem. Because you just said their situation, circumstance, feelings, opinions, and ideas about THEIR OWN BODY were less important than your personal comfort and preferences. Medical freedom means the freedom to make ANY/ALL medical decisions about your health and your body. Even if other people don't like it. Even if it could someday, in some situation, affect someone else. Even if it's flat-out stupid. Freedom is ALL THE TIME. It "weakens" the argument to pretend otherwise, to want mandates for some things you agree with but want freedom on other decisions. Because it's easy to stand up for freedom when it's a choice you want to be able to make, but not at all easy to stand up when it's a choice you think should be controlled. We stand for medical freedom always.

column31: These days, around 70% of women get epidurals when they're in labor, and that number has been increasing steadily for years. But do women really know what is in the epidural...or the potential risks they face? Regardless of what any woman chooses, she deserves full, complete informed choice. Most epidurals are a combination of two drugs: bupivacaine and fentanyl. The medication does cross the placenta and get to the baby, but the effects on babies aren't well-studied. Some old studies show that babies were a bit irritable or "difficult" in the first few days after birth, and that this affected bonding and maternal perception of motherhood, but there aren't more recent studies to confirm or deny this. Maternal risks are more clear. There's an increased risk of both instrument-assisted delivery and caesarean delivery. Plus, many women develop fevers, low blood pressure, dizziness, nausea, and may have slightly longer labors. Babies are more likely to be malpositioned. Of course, in some cases, moms can get exhausted or tense from pain, and an epidural might be what allows them to keep laboring and deliver successfully. There are different blends of pain medications and different amounts given, and lower levels of pain medications -- sometimes referred to as "walking epidurals" -- seem to have fewer risks for mom with good outcomes for mom and baby. If you are considering an epidural, ask questions about what kind of medication you would be given, the dose, and how much control you would have over it. Explore non-drug options as well. Antibody-Dependent Disease Enhancement (ADE) Coronavirus vaccines have a long history of “enhancing disease”. Vaccines generating antibodies against SARS-CoV-2 may bind to the virus without neutralizing it. Should this happen, the non-neutralizing antibodies could enhance viral entry into cells and viral replication and end up worsening infection instead of offering protection, through the poorly understood phenomenon of ADE. In a 1960s vaccine trial, 80% of infants and young children immunized against RSV (respiratory syncytial virus, an RNA virus in the family Paramyxoviridae) ended up hospitalized, and 2 children died. Where 5% of the children in the control group required hospitalization. column31: “It’s time to put a face back on the plate.” That’s how my friend, Dr. Bill Schindler puts it. Years ago, I don’t think I would have understood this concept. I was more concerned with the nutrient density of foods and how they would nourish my body. I didn’t think twice about its provenance. 😑 Now, tho, after interviewing countless farmers, visiting farms, &, enjoying their meat & produce, it has become very clear to me that where our food comes from REALLY matters. And it’s important to reconnect with that reality. I know there’s a big difference between meat we buy at the store on a styrofoam tray (even if labeled “organic” or “grass-fed”) & that which is pasture-raised, grass-fed, grass-finished on a local farm that follows regenerative farm practices. But I went to to process the bison & to the roast the following night to grow in awareness about what it costs for meat to be on my plate. This bison gave his life last week to nourish a group of us. We respected him as we processed his body w/ gratitude. (See my IG story for more on the experience.) Here, I am thanking him for his sacrifice. 🙏 Does it matter to you where your food comes from? Do you know your farmer? Do you WANT to put a face back on the plate? Tell me below. Just wondering. No judgment. P.S. Listen to Wise Traditions podcast 231: “Eating Nose to Tail” w/ Bill Schindler 🎧 for more perspective on what we stand to lose when disconnected from our food. 🧡🧡🧡 Hay que regresar a las raíces de nuestra comida. Pasé el fin de semana pasado en una granja donde procesamos a un bisonte. Yo no sabía que esperar, francamente. Soy carnívora pero nunca había presenciado algo parecido. (Véanse mis historias para más detalles. ) Lo que sí sé es que estamos demasiado desconectados con el origen de nuestra comida. Por eso yo decidí tomar el paso de no sólo presenciar el acto de sacrificio sino de participar en él. Sé que le cuesta al animal dar su vida para nutrirme. A poco es mucho para mí agradecerle y conocer algo de la suya? Has procesado antes a un animal? Sí o no? Y que opinas de la idea de que nos acerquemos más a la fuente de lo que se encuentra en nuestro plato?

column31: Friends, Summer is here which is wonderful! And we really need to get outdoors to get the health benefits from sunshine and fresh air right now with this unnecessary lockdown. However, I cringe when others shout "use your sunscreen!!" as if they are all safe and the same. Or seeing parents spraying their kids with the spray sunscreen (proven to be one of the most toxic). And never with a disclaimer that store bought one's contain cancer causing chemicals, it's proven. And to use a safe and healthy sunscreen. Fun fact about me...I use to burn like a lobster in my earlier years when I was a carboholic. I used to eat bread (like loaves in a week), crackers, premade waffles, pancakes, toast, toast and more toast, boxed cereal, fast-food weekly (yes!), deli meats, ... salad dressings, frozen meals, chips, chips and more chips, microwave french fries all day long, anything carby starchy and processed, I ate it ... all *doused* in inflammatory rancid canola and other vegetable oils and other chemicals. And I was sick constantly with one issue or another. Since then, I have changed my lifestyle - I eat grass fed meats (naturally high in healthy omega 3,6 and 9's), salmon, avocado, grass fed real butter, olive oil (even slather from head to toe daily), coconut oil, avocado oil, lots of pasture raised eggs, low OX greens, lots of therapeutic supplements and many essential oils daily. And guess what? Not only do I NOT burn anymore, but my skin tans a pretty golden brown, I actually use olive oil on my skin in the sun ...and my immune system is iron clad and I feel amazing. Let's talk *Mineral* Sunscreen vs. toxic Chemical Sunscreen + learn how to "eat" your sunscreen ☀️😎 There are two ways that a sunscreen can protect the skin from sun damage: with a mineral barrier or a chemical one. Mineral sunscreens typically include ingredients like zinc oxide or titanium dioxide, which create a physical barrier to protect the skin from the sun. Chemical sunscreens use one or more chemicals including oxybenzone, avobenzone, octisalate, octocrylene, homosalate and octinoxate (all linked to hormone disruption and cancers). PROBLEM: Reasons not to use chemical sunscreens: 1. The sunscreen chemicals raise some series concerns because most are able to cross into skin and other tissues - You probably know my stance: if you can’t eat it, you shouldn’t put it on your skin. 2. The chemicals create free radicals that have been linked to cancers and the chemicals are absorbed into your entire body via your largest organs > your skin. 3. Many of these chemicals are considered hormone disruptors. Hormone disruptors can affect how estrogen and other hormones act in the body, by blocking them or mimicking them, which throws off the body's hormonal balance. column31: Let's talk primal brain and prefrontal cortex and how they relate to our food choice success and drive, the importance of planning what you’re going to eat ahead of time and how to manage urges! I work with a lot of clients across the US with insulin resistance, many in early stages unbeknownst to them [and mood concerns]. It affects the signals in our bodies in terms of hunger and fullness and many times they are not accurate in the sense that we have completely thrown our bodies off by the food [and chemicals] that we have put into them; mainly sugar, flour, sugars and refined and processed foods that our hormones and neurotransmitters don’t really know what to do with them. When we’re eating those types of foods and then we start to try and tune into our body, our hunger signals, our hormones and cell receptor sites are so off that we feel like we’re hungry all of the time. So even though we may be eating only when we’re hungry, we’re eating too much because our body is actually craving food that it doesn’t actually need for fuel. Stick to healthy fats, proteins and low OX vegetables = high voltage foods! We make decisions primarily via two types of brain regions 👇 1.) Prefrontal cortex/modern brain (front). Problem solving, memory, language, judgment, impulse control, reasoning, long term goals, thoughtfulness, personal growth decisions and creating the best version of you. Adult brain. 2.) Primal/primitive/reptilian brain (basal ganglia)(hind). What is satisfying and gratifying NOW and in the moment, survival, drive and instinct. Toddler brain. Letting the primal brain make decisions (unless it's an emergency) is a tragedy. It leads to weight gain and overindulgence and buffering in a way that causes us tons of results that we don’t want. What you need to do is look at the brain decision-making process and utilize the most powerful part of your human brain, which is your prefrontal cortex. That is the part of your brain that separates you from animalistic behavior, primal behavior. That is the part of the brain where you can look ahead and you can plan and you can make decisions as an emotional adult. I like to compare it to the difference between a toddler and an adult. You can look into the future, delay gratification, give up what you want now for what you want most. You can take care of yourself even though you may not feel the immediate gratification from it. Plan out your meals ahead of time and stick to that plan.🍽 If we’re not planning ahead in terms of what we’re going to put in our body, that means relying on our primal brain to make those decisions in the moment and it’s completely unfair to our future self because the primal brain will always choose immediate pleasure. That is its job. And if you don’t override it with your prefrontal, human, higher level brain, you will be always at the effect of instant gratification. Because there’s so much instant gratification available, you will over-consume, which will create undesirable effect in the way you feel and probably in the way you carry your weight. There are several steps to this, however, step one is going to really be about utilizing that prefrontal. The concept is, losing weight is a *series* of small decisions. Those decisions need to be made from your higher brain. Small decisions throughout the day, lead us to that big wonderful outcome. Stay the course with eating the health nutrient dense low carbohydrate food you have planned out ahead - and don't diverge, that's the primal (toddler brain) saying ...just do it! . . column31: We're tired of this stupid line. Science is never "settled." We may think we have a consensus, for now, based on what we currently know, but we *always* acknowledge there is more to know and keep asking questions. In the 1700s, one doctor had a little bit of a "crazy" idea. You see, women who were delivering babies in a medical ward with experienced doctors were dying in high numbers, while women who were delivering with students or midwives weren't. Semmelweiss came up with the theory that women were dying because doctors were performing autopsies and transferring "pieces of disease" to the women giving birth. Naturally, this was considered ridiculous and Semmelweiss was scoffed at. There was no such thing as "pieces of disease" and there was no way that performing autopsies just before attending to these women had anything to do with them dying. Still, he persisted, and got them to try washing their hands in between the autopsies and helping the women. Guess what? The death rate plummeted. Semmelweiss had been vindicated! Only...no. The doctors dismissed the data and went back to their old ways, and women began dying in high numbers again. Semmelweiss was told he was crazy, and was committed to a mental institution. It would be decades before someone else posited the same theory, and it eventually became accepted that hand-washing was, in fact, an important way to prevent the spread of disease. Often times, people who sound the alarm or speak out against "settled science" are dismissed, mocked, or considered crazy. But if they don't speak up, things never get better. It is the minority voices, pushing for *real* science and demanding proper studies and answers to questions that are truly changing the world. Not those clinging to the past and considering science to be "settled."

column36:
California cannot reopen schools unless they are safe.

The following letter was sent to Governor Gavin Newsom, Assembly Speaker Anthony Rendon, Senate Pro Tem Toni Atkins and Superintendent of Public Instruction Tony Thurmond:

Honorable California Leaders, 

We write on behalf of the 310,000 members of the California Teachers Association and the more than nine million students we serve regarding the pending reopening of schools and colleges throughout the state. We appreciate your leadership and efforts in meeting this extraordinary challenge. We understand the dramatic impact of the pandemic on the state budget and appreciate all efforts to protect public education, while recognizing that the budget relies on $13 billion in deferrals and additional federal funding. It is why, looking forward, we believe the state must have additional revenues to address the growing needs. 

Since schools closed in March, CTA has said that the health and safety of our students and educators must always be our top priority and our guiding principle during this crisis. Much is still being learned about the COVID-19 virus. The recent surge in the infection rate and the closure of indoor activities in 26 counties gives us pause around the state’s preparedness for safe in-person school instruction in a short six- to eight-week time frame. In this current situation, we believe that the “Precautionary Principle” should guide us. This means taking the most preventative action in the face of uncertainty to protect students, educators, and our communities. Simply said, California cannot reopen schools unless they are safe.

Unfortunately, many local districts and communities don’t have the necessary resources or capacity to maintain even the most basic prevention measures of six feet physical distancing and limiting contacts, much less the other important preventative actions such as personal protective equipment (PPE), testing and tracing, or adequate ventilation and cleaning supplies.

While no one method of prevention by itself is 100 percent effective, layered strategies boost prevention with each measure knocking off some percentage of exposure and potential infection. This includes a clear and manageable plan to implement measures like physical distancing of six feet, reducing the number of contacts, face coverings, handwashing, daily health screening, support for sick and at-risk people to stay at home, robust testing, good ventilation (with absolutely no recirculated air), and cleaning and disinfecting.

We should be clear-eyed about this reality. How can we physically reopen schools with lower thresholds of safety than we currently have for restaurants or hair salons?

Safe school reopening will require the state to coordinate consistent public health department operations that offer a uniform symptoms checklist and safety protocols; data transparency and accessibility; increased testing dedicated to schools for students and staff; rapid case notification and contact tracing; isolation support and medical care for our most vulnerable students and families; and health monitoring of students to serve as early understandings of transmissions in schools and warnings of any school-based outbreaks. We also ask the state to direct the California Department of Public Health to coordinate with CalOSHA to develop and implement training for all school districts on safety protocols and to direct that Illness and Injury Prevention plans be updated and adopted prior to the first day of in-person instruction.

As educators, we too want to be back with our students doing the work that we love, but we cannot ignore science, facts, and safety. Absent a specific plan for each school that includes a clear line of responsibility and accountability we have two options:

1. A high-risk in-person opening, even under a hybrid model. 
2. Start the new school year under robust distance learning protocols until the virus is contained in local communities and proper safety measures can be put into place.

It is clear that communities and school districts have not come close to meeting the threshold for a safe return to in-person learning, even under a hybrid model. In fact, with recent health orders issued in 26 counties impacting nearly 85 percent of Californians, we are going backwards. How can we reasonably expect hundreds of students, and in some cases more than 1,000 students, to come together on one campus for an entire day without putting their health and the lives of every adult on that campus at risk? Federal and state guidance regarding a phased reopening have focused on a sustained downward trajectory of COVID-19 cases for 14 days or no more than 1 COVID-19 case per 10,000 in the past 14 days. From a public health perspective, the best course of action would be to focus on improving our ability to provide robust, quality distance learning until the virus is marginalized and safety measures are addressed.

In a few months, we’ve gone from:

Everyone must stay home for two weeks and businesses must close so that we don’t overwhelm hospitals... 

While thousands of medical professionals perform dances on TikTok, the CDC changes COVID case and death definitions to include almost ANYONE, thousands of patients are inappropriately placed on ventilators and die needlessly, and Governor Cuomo and others send COVID patients to infect our most vulnerable in nursing homes, driving up the number of cases and deaths. 

To: 

Even though we “flattened the curve”, even though most hospitals were never even close to being overwhelmed, that there’s a high percentage who have little to no symptoms (including children), and that the infection fatality rate is akin to the flu...

The powers that be are going to wreak havoc on the country by spreading fear and division, force you to wear masks in public which weaken your immune system, encourage you to feel hatred for your family and friends who choose not to wear masks, and make you distance yourself from others in your community, because they’re hoping this will work to slow the development of herd immunity, and increase demand for a COVID vaccine...

Because well, how bad would that be if they wasted the billions of dollars Bill Gates invested in it?

————

Remember, the lockdown was never meant to reduce the number of overall deaths from COVID-19. Just to not overwhelm hospitals for a short period of time. That’s it. We all knew that cases would rise after the lockdown ended. And really, who knows how many “cases” were even confirmed with a test (which is faulty in and of itself), and how many are “probable”? 

Ultimately, we are being forced to do all of these things because they want to push the vaccine.

Even though the vaccine is being rushed at “warp speed” with zero long term safety trials, they will claim it is “safe and effective”. They will claim it can prevent deaths from COVID. No doubt, until the vaccine is rolled out, they will try to strong arm the rest of us into submission - to wear masks, to accept that schools will no longer be a place for your child that is fun and provides connection with their peers, but feels more like a detention center, where you don’t get too close, you don’t dare step out of line, you don’t get to smile at your friends because they can’t even see your face. No smiling anymore, no hugging, no high fives, no real human connection of any kind for the majority of their days. 

I am shocked and dismayed that people are ok with this. Because we are being told that it’s for our “protection”.

We are being manipulated and controlled in unimaginable ways right now.

column31: "Detoxing" is really popular in the natural health community, but that means that advice -- some of it well-meaning, but mistaken -- flies around a lot. Here are some of the top myths we hear...and the truth explained! #1: Harsh cleanses are the best way. Definitely not. Harsh cleanses are unnecessary and can even be dangerous. Depending on how they are done, they can tank your metabolism, release a bunch of stored toxins that can't be excreted (causing further damage to your organs), and redistribute toxins in your body. Don't do this. #2: You can't detox while pregnant or breastfeeding. You ARE detoxing while pregnant and breastfeeding literally 24/7 because your body does that to stay alive. Harsh cleanses are not safe at this time, but they really aren't safe ever (see #1). "Detoxes" that aim to support your body's natural processes are safe while pregnant and breastfeeding. #3: You have to take a lot of supplements or follow a "plan" Yes, it's easier, especially if you are new to the topic, to want to follow someone else's strictly laid-out plan. And some companies will sell you very expensive kits where you have to take several different supplements in a certain order for several days or weeks. This is rarely necessary. Many things you can do with what you have at home or can find at a grocery store. There are inexpensive products that can support your efforts as well. We offer a free download that explains some options and a handful of inexpensive, optional products to help support you. #4: It's not possible/necessary to "detox" Some people think that because your body naturally detoxes itself to stay alive, that you can't and shouldn't do any kind of detox in addition to that. Well, that would be great, if people weren't experiencing symptoms due to toxicity, but they are. Toxicity symptoms may include frequent headaches, brain fog, lack of energy, weight gain, poor-quality sleep, and more. When your detox organs are overburdened, you need to do something about that. #5: Detoxes without lifestyle changes will fix your health Sorry, but there are no quick fixes. Doing a crash diet and cleanse for a few days, then going right back to eating junk, living under tons of stress, and never exercising will not help you. Oh, you may feel better for a short period of time, but this doesn't solve your problem. You must commit to doing better *all* the time in order to feel better all the time! If we can help...just ask!

column31: Most women will face a gestational diabetes test somewhere around their 28th week of pregnancy. But do you know all the facts about GD...and the test itself? In America, a two-step test is generally used. A 1-hour "glucose challenge test" with 50 g sugar (or GCT), followed by a 3-hour "glucose tolerance test" with 100 g sugar (or GTT) if the first one is failed. That first test doesn't require fasting, so results can be pretty far off for some women, depending on what else they've eaten that day. Plus, women who usually eat low-sugar or low-carb diets may fail because their bodies aren't used to dealing with a huge load of sugar. A better approach is to look at a woman's risk factors -- being over 25, having a family history of diabetes, being overweight, having a fasting blood sugar higher than 95. A woman without these risk factors doesn't need the test, as she has less than 1% chance of having GD. In most other countries, a 2-hour fasting test with 75 g sugar is used, which is a better approach for at-risk women. It's also worth noting the diagnostic criteria has shifted over time, and there's still no consensus on exactly what numbers qualify a woman as having GD, which can mean there is some under- or over-diagnosis. The glucola drink that women are given is filled with terrible ingredients, and has an immediate negative impact on many women. A lot feel sick and awful during the test, and may vomit -- which negates the test results. Many doctors say there aren't alternatives, but that isn't true. Studies have been done using different forms of candy (Twizzlers and jelly beans) as well as meals calculated to the right amount of carbs. These alternatives were just as good in providing a correct diagnosis, and were tolerated much better. Prevalence of gestational diabetes is increasing, as mothers are heavier and older. In some populations, prevalence is under 2%. In others, it's over 26%, a 13-fold increase. For many women, diet can help control GD. Avoiding sugar and refined carbs makes a big difference. For about 50% of women, they eventually end up needing insulin (the studies weren't clear whether diet changes didn't work or if women didn't want/weren't able to make them -- probably some of both). Interestingly, some studies have been done on using nutritional supplements in women who were diagnosed with GD. They found that magnesium, in particular, was associated with significant reductions in fasting blood sugar, insulin sensitivity, markers of inflammation, and pregnancy outcomes. Newborns were 4x less likely to have jaundice or be hospitalized. Vitamin D and E, calcium, and zinc were all shown to be beneficial as well. The bottom line? Many women could get away with examining their risk factors and checking their fasting blood sugar once to see if they might have GD, and not need any further testing. If testing is needed, healthier alternatives to the 'glucola' can and should be used (and the 2-hr fasting test is better than the 1-hr non-fasting test). Eating healthy and avoiding refined carbs and simple sugars, and getting plenty of magnesium is key. column36:
This was the day that changed my life forever. This day I didn’t realize that I was hurting my children by what I thought was the “right thing to do.”

My little one in this picture received her hep a vaccine at her 2 year well. 2 weeks later was having rapid heart rate and belly breathing. Was not sick, or anything. She spent the night in hospital for observation because after two back to back breathing treatments and a steroid, her breathing did not improve. We were released the following day with to continue steroid and treatments and within a week or so it stabilized. Fast forward two weeks from there she began screaming and crying in the middle of the night. Waking up in extreme belly pain and leg pain. Over the next month she couldn’t sit on her butt, she couldn’t climb a chair or on a couch, things she was so good at before with no fear. Between all this time and constant pain, no sleep etc we went and saw our ped who kept telling me she was constipated. I begged for MRI or some kind of imaging and she basically said i was crazy. She was to the point she could no longer walk or take a few steps without falling down. She issued blood work and everything was normal, no indication of her fighting off infection. I got fed up and took her to ER with little help there too. They did a X-ray and did show her backed up. For almost a month she was fed miralax 2 full caps a day and was not working. Finally self referred myself to a GI doctor since my ped was shit. He listened to me for ONE hour. Immediately ordered an MRI because he could tell the fear in me. Took two weeks to schedule MRI. Within hours they called and told me they found someone on her spine to take her to hospital she was being admitted. Next day she under went another MRI and spinal tap. 

She was diagnosed with Guillain Barre Syndrome at two years old. She spent 6 days at the hospital receiving IVIG. She at that point could barely walk without falling over. Her speech was affected and she was slurring words. IVIG thank god helped her. 

It’s been almost a year since hospital stay and me advocating for my girls. I’m so sick of people posting vaccinate your damn kids. I did, and look where that ended us up. Since this she has brain lesions that will hopefully fade in time. We have seen oncology who don’t believe it’s cancer. Looking at this post, if I could go back to the beginning I would of changed it all.

column31: So what does medical freedom mean to you? To us it means this - We respect the individuals right to make ANY medical choice, in ANY situation, no matter what. It's not our job to tell anyone else how to take care of their health, even if we strongly disagree. column31: Do you feel tired and sluggish all the time, even though you're getting plenty of sleep? Does your mood fluctuate throughout the day? Do you crave salty foods? You could be suffering from adrenal fatigue. This term was coined in 1998 by James Wilson, PhD, a naturopath and expert in alternative medicine. Adrenal Fatigue is group of related signs and symptoms (a syndrome) that results when the adrenal glands function below the necessary level. It’s usually associated with intense stress and often follows chronic infections like bronchitis, flu, or pneumonia. More signs of adrenal fatigue include: -abnormal fatigue -blood sugar roller coaster -excessive crankiness -weight gain or loss -insomnia or other sleep disturbances -lack of interest in sex -hair loss It is very important to get our adrenal health under control. Check out this article for tips on how to recover from adrenal fatigue, and enjoy excellent health! https://modernalternativemama.com/2010/09/21/diet-for-adrenal-health/

column31: San Quentin Prison in CA had ZERO covid-19 cases throughout this entire pandemic until the end of May. On May 30, 121 inmates were transferred to San Quentin from Chino, where a coronavirus outbreak was raging. These men WERE NOT TESTED prior to being placed in San Quentin. "The inmates were issued cloth masks, which they wore during the transfer, and have remained segregated together in a 14-day quarantine since their arrival while they undergo additional testing for the virus." But these measures DID NOT WORK. Now one month later there are 1,021 cases of Covid-19 at San Quentin, including 89 staff members. Governor Newsom has stated he plans on releasing more inmates back into the community: 3,500 have been released so far, and 3,500 more have potential to be released. The Governor identified 110 inmates who are eligible for early release from San Quentin, a prison where one in three inmates have tested positive for coronavirus. Around the nation, prisons are hotbeds for outbreaks. Nine out of the 10 known largest clusters of the virus are in correctional institutions. Of the total cases of coronavirus, Texas’ prison population account for over 7,000 cases, Ohio’s prisons account for 4,900, Michigan’s prisons account for 3,991 and Federal prisons have 6,621. Tennessee’s prisons have 3,171 cases, New Jersey has 2,756. According to NYT, more than 80,000 people in prison have tested positive for coronavirus. Ironically, according to Reuters, up to 95% of prisoners who test positive had no symptoms. In Ohio, of the 2,028 who tested positive, close to 95% had no symptoms. In four state prison systems — Arkansas, North Carolina, Ohio and Virginia — 96% of 3,277 inmates who tested positive for the coronavirus were asymptomatic. https://www.themarshallproject.org/2020/05/01/a-state-by-state-look-at-coronavirus-in-prisons https://www.latimes.com/california/story/2020-06-30/california-coronavirus-inmate-release https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2020/06/29/san-quentin-coronavirus-outbreak-nearly-one-third-inmates/3283450001/ https://www.mercurynews.com/2020/06/09/inmates-moved-to-san-quentin-test-positive-for-Covid-19:=:https://www.mercurynews.com/2020/06/09/inmates-moved-to-san-quentin-test-positive-for-Covid-19/

column31: There is growing objection to the National Park Service efforts to expand connectivity as an important visitor amenity. The opponents claim it violates the law and NPS mandate. The most vocal and dogged opponent of the cellular build-out is Public Employees for Environmental Responsibility (PEER), which over the past decade has barraged the Park Service with complaints, Freedom of Information Act requests, and, when ignored, FOIA lawsuits regarding its cell-siting decisions. It quotes NEPA and The Wilderness Act as the basis for the claims. The Wireless Act defines wilderness as "an area where the earth and its community of life are untrammeled by man, where man himself is a visitor who does not remain." The article claims that bringing cell towers into the parks would violate the act which also says that, "There shall be no commercial enterprise . . . within any wilderness area designated by this Act." PEER sees the connectivity controversy as part of a loss of direction of the agency and its mandate. The article unfortunately does not mention the adverse health effects of this wireless deployment.

column31: The Chinese government has approved an experimental COVID-19 vaccine for its military associated with some troubling adverse events in a study that came out in May. From the article: Previous results of Ad5-nCoV trials, published in medical journal the Lancet, were met with a lukewarm response by experts. According to the study, almost half of Ad5-nCoV vaccine recipients reported fever, with 44% describing fatigue and 39% reporting a headache. Overall, 9% of patients described side effects that were severe enough to have potentially "prevented activity."
